Persistent: an object whose data is stored in a metakit row.

class StorageManager(object):
    def request_storage(self, object):
        return view, rownum

class Persistent(object):
    def __init__(self, storage, view, ):
        self.storage = storage

    

__init__(self, project, store=(view, rownum))
self._view is a metakit view.
self._rownum is the row index.
self._data is a metakit rowref.

If it is called with store=None (new object):
    store = project.request_storage(self)
